reviewText: Not really what I was expecting. After watching Hunting Marsh Bucks I thought this would be just as, or close to being as informative... nope... not at all. If youve seen the marsh bucks dvd, this is pretty much all repetitive info. If you haven't seen the marsh bucks dvd, buy that instead. For some reason the Dan guy is not in this one, and I feel that is what made the other dvds so much more informative. Also, this dvd pushed a lot of crap products, unlike some of their other stuff... maybe that's why Dan isn't in this one...
This is a great DVDs! Lots of good info and great examples during actual hunts of the strategies discussed
Good video on Hunting but not as good as hill country bucks

This is by far the best bow hunting video I have watched. I DVR any and every whitetail shows on outdoor, sportsmen and pursuit channel. None are even close to this with information. No infomercials, just killing whitetail strategies. Priceless knowledge in an easy to follow format with an easy to use dvd  menu. Stop thinking and buy thus video. You won't regret it. -Jason Collins NW Missouri

This is not your typical watch me shoot a big deer video where its more production than anything.  This video is a great teaching tool that shows you how and why the set ups worked.  All in all a good video worth the price.

This isn't just your "bed to food source" mainstream crap.  This isn't about sponsors.  It is just a handful of extremely successful hunters sharing in depth details about hunting strategy.  Must buy video
